  "bodyHtml": "<style>body{margin:0;font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;background:#f8fafc;color:#0f172a}header{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0f172a,#1e293b);padding:90px 20px;text-align:center;color:#fff}header h1{margin:0;font-size:42px;font-weight:700}header p{margin-top:20px;font-size:18px;color:#cbd5e1}article{max-width:1100px;margin:auto;padding:80px 20px;line-height:1.9}h2{margin-top:60px;font-size:28px;color:#0f172a}p{margin-top:20px;color:#334155}footer{background:#0f172a;padding:50px 20px;text-align:center;color:#cbd5e1;margin-top:60px}</style><header><h1>Charity Tech & Nonprofit Digital Infrastructure</h1><p>Artificial Intelligence • Fundraising Platforms • Secure Payments • Cloud Infrastructure • Technology for Good</p></header><article><p>Charity technology in 2026 represents the backbone of modern nonprofit impact. Advanced digital systems power fundraising optimisation, secure donation processing, volunteer management automation and transparent impact reporting. AI analytics, encrypted cloud infrastructure and scalable digital ecosystems allow mission-driven organisations to operate with enterprise-level efficiency.</p><h2>AI & Predictive Fundraising</h2><p>Machine learning models forecast donor behaviour, optimise outreach campaigns and improve retention rates. Natural language systems assist grant writing and supporter communication.</p><h2>Secure Infrastructure & Compliance</h2><p>Modern nonprofit platforms integrate encryption-by-default, multi-factor authentication and zero-trust architecture to protect donor data.</p><h2>Cloud & Scalable Systems</h2><p>Hybrid cloud environments provide resilience and global availability for digital donation platforms.</p></article><footer>© 2026 Sitters4Charities • Technology for Good</footer><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\n\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\n\"@graph\":[\n{\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"@id\":\"https://sitters4charities.org/#website\",\"url\":\"https://sitters4charities.org/\",\"name\":\